  physical_appearance: This is a black-and-white photograph. It features a group of shoulder under a roofed shelter. The background of the photograph shows a clearing in a dense forest. In the shelter
 the soldier on the right is proning on the ground
 while aiming a weapon towards the left. Behind him
 there are three other soldiers seated casually
 and one soldier lying down on the left. The photograph is torn
 especially on the top left and right corners.

  sgcool_label_text: A variety of portraits of British soldiers that show them at leisure as well as two photographs of James Steele placing a wreath at a remembrance ceremony
 this collection is part of the archive of James Steele
 Royal Artillery (Field) who served in Malaya from January 1941-February 1942
 when interned as a P.O.W at Changi until his release in October 1945.
